\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\li180\ri-2162
\cf0 \
It will report the track selected to play first. If you have not selected a track in the selected playlist then playing will commence with the 
\b first
\b0  track in the playlist.\
\
Enter the number of seconds to wait between each track and click the "OK" button. The tracks will play.\
\
\'95 The applet stays running while it manages playback. After the last track of the playlist starts playing the applet will quit.\
\
\'95 Tracks in the playlist which cannot be "played" (Books, PDFs, "continuous" URL tracks, and so on) will be skipped.\
\
\'95 To 
\b Quit
\b0  the applet manually, Control-click or click-and-hold its icon in the Dock and choose "Quit" from the menu that appears; or, select the applet and choose "Quit A Space Between" from its application menu.\
\
\'95 The applet is equipped with a "dead-man's switch". If, for some reason, a track does not begin playing after a reasonable amount of time (4 x the delay factor, actually) the applet will quit.\
\
\
