\b\fs36 \cf2 How's It Work?
\b0\fs24 \cf0 \
\
The applet plays each track using the AppleScript 
\b play
\b0  command's 
\b once
\b0  parameter. When that song has finished playing, iTunes is stopped. The applet detects that iTunes is stopped (it checks for this once per second in an 
\b idle
\b0  handler) and then uses a 
\b delay 
\i n
\i0\b0  command (where 
\i n
\i0  is seconds) before playing the next track in the play order. And so on.\
\
\
